metadata.name: Snell's Artifacts #8
metadata.description:
Snell's artifacts are imaginary geometric objects created using Snell's and Descartes' laws of optics that define the behavior of a ray of light passing from one transparent medium to another.

By applying these laws to extreme parameters, beyond what the real world is capable of producing and with a high level of variability, we open the door to a new world.

In order to keep some control over this extreme and crazy world, the grid within which the rays evolve is divided into several squares. Each of these squares limits the grid settings at that location.

In order to be able to generate a Snell Artifact, 1 to 6 million rays are created. It may take a while. So be patient while these radii are calculated.




Keyboard commands:
[S]: Saves a PNG image of 4000x4000 pixels without glow filter
[SHIFT + S]: Saves a 4000x4000 pixel PNG image and applies a glow filter (may take a long time depending on your system)

URL parameters:
Add the parameter size=N to generate an image of NxN pixels (glow effect will be disabled by default)
Add the parameter glow=true to apply a glow effect to the image




Artist: Estienne
July 2022

metadata.name: Coded Tiny Dinos #431
metadata.description:
Coded Tiny Dinos.

Inspired from Tiny Dinos collection which are cc0 (copyright waived), they are pfp with layered images.

Coded Tiny Dinos do not use any form of images, they are fully made with code, making them layers free pfp image made just with code and generated based on the hash.

You can check the code for yourself.

(I have asked the moderation team if i can publish this project, they said yes on a condition i mention everything in the description)

metadata.name: redline #171
metadata.description:
This is my second generative art project on fxhash. I wanted a project that offered more VARIETY compared for my first project so this is what I came up with: a clean and simple rectangles & lines project :D 

There are a few options for the number of columns that are generated: 3, 5, 7, 9, and each column is randomly filled with dense or alternating line patterns (sometimes no pattern!). 3 columns are common, the rest are less common. Having more than half the columns empty is relatively rare. Having all columns empty is extremely rare! 

Also I have to give credit to Tyler Hobbs, this piece was super inspired by an old IG post of his. Please enjoy!

metadata.name: musical society #29
metadata.description:
society.png: musical society is a collaborative PFP work drawn by Tito Yusuf and directed by Sandy Pirouzi with the aim to facilitate Tezos newcomers with affordable PFP to rock.

This series is taking inspiration from a music scene that Tito is part of. Some traits are paying tribute to some of Tezos musicians such as Jburn, Musical Jackal, Binerica, and Sigmun.

---------------------------------------------
  Most will be us
Some are pretending to be us
Some others are even not us
(And few of them are not even alive anymore)
---------------------------------------------

  PS Tito is a master at bad drawing. Don’t expect fine lines with perfect alignment in his drawing (but the colors are fun!).

  PPS There’s no utility in this project except the CC0 license, so just have fun with it ;)  

Special thanks to:
 purespider for the template and assistance
Jburn, IndraAziz (Musical Jackal), Binerica, Mirffu (Sigmun) for allowing the making and usage of respective traits
ciphrd and fx(hash) team for allowing the making and usage of fx(hash) traits

 Type: Image Composition
 Dimension: 1000 x 1000 px
License for visual: CC0 
License for code: MIT

Twitter: @titoys90 @spirouzi

metadata.name: Elementary Cellular Emoji Automata #768
metadata.description:
Features the full set of 1761 emojis, including skin tone and gender modifiers and all flags.
Arranged using the full 256 ruleset of one-dimensional cellular automata

If “random seed” is true then the seed of the generation is randomized using Math.random() meaning that the pattern will change on regeneration.
The ruleset, emoji, colors and all other properties will remain the same.

Auto-adjusts to screen size

Compatible with as many browsers and systems as possible

metadata.name: Homage to Capogrossi #3
metadata.description:
This is an homage to one of my favourite artists of all times. 
I wanted to create something that mimicked his style, without pretending to contain his spirit. 
Studying his masterpieces to write this code gave me the opportunity to dive into his gaze; I have understood some things but the most important and interesting part remains obscure.

There are four main templates and infinite compositions.
Two templates have backgrounds of two different colours.

"S" to save 1400x1400

Created with P5.js by Carla Chicchiero

metadata.name: The dice is cast #18
metadata.description:
When I started studying the code and learning the "random" functions in early July 2022, it made me think of randomness when throwing dice. It is random, but with these restrictions (3 six-sided dice = 216 possibilities). 

With this mindset and theme, I began to create this first attempt at generative art. 

In my usual work, I take everyday objects, materials, etc. and play with them. For this series, I inserted blocks of polystyrene to give it substance. 

All the graphic elements, colours and random arrangements were created using P5.js. The photos of polystyrene and the dices are integrated.

Press ENTER to download as a jpg image. 

@Yomu Oyashi July 2022

The NFT licence 2.0
